<item>
            <title>[LU-17478] parallelize unaligned writes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17478</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Unaligned DIO/hybrid IO writes are not currently parallel, which severely limits their performance (to around 3 GiB/s with 20 GiB/s DIO).&#160; With the fix from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17085&quot; title=&quot;llite: safely duplicate iov_iter (was: pin_user_pages on unaligned DIO/AIO)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17085&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17085&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, this becomes possible, and it turns out it can be done fairly easily.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
